der-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">l = [student_1, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">56754</span>, <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'hello\'</span>]\nl = [[<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">2</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">3</span>], [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">4</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">5</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">6</span>]]\nl = [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span> == <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">2</span>, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span> == <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>] <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># l contains [False, True]</span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">create an empty list</p>\n\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">l = []\nl = list() <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># the list constructor</span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">create a list by applying a function to every member of a sequence, called a list comprehension</p>\n\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">l = [f(x) <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">for</span> x <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">in</span> sequence]\nl = [x*<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">2</span> <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">for</span> x <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">in</span> range(<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">6</span>)] <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># [2,4,6,8,10]</span>\nl = [<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\"${:.2f}\"</span>.format(x) <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">for</span> x <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">in</span> [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1.10343</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">5.59730</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">4.35467</span>]]\n<span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># [\'$1.10\', \'$5.60\', \'$4.35\']</span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">or by casting another sequence into a list type</p>\n\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">l = list(<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'hello\'</span>) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># [\'h\',\'e\',\'l\',\'l\',\'o\']</span>\nl = list((<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">2</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">3</span>)) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># [1,2,3]</span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"use-lists\" style=\"margin: 1.3em 0px 1em; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.4em; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: #cccccc;\">use lists</h2>\n<ul style=\"margin: 1.2em 0px; padding-left: 2em;\">\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">lists have a zero-based index, and slice notation is used to access one or more objects in the list</p>\n\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">l[<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">0</span>] <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># first item in list</span>\nl[:<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">2</span>] <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># first two items in list; same as l[0:2]</span>\nl[<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">3</span>:<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">6</span>] <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># the fourth, fifth, and sixth items</span>\nl[-<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>] <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># last item in list</span>\nl[<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">5</span>:] <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># the sixth item until the end; same as l[5:len(l)]</span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">add a step parameter to get every second object, every third object, etc.</p>\n\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">l[::<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">2</span>] <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># every other item in list</span>\nl[<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>:<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">8</span>:<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">3</span>] <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># every third item in slice [1:8]</span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">index gets the index of the first occurrence of the argument</p>\n\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">l = [<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'hello\'</span>,<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'world\'</span>, <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'world\'</span>]\nl.index(<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'world\'</span>) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># returns 1</span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">loop through lists using standard for-in loops</p>\n\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\"><span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">for</span> x <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">in</span> nums:\n    print(<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'x= \'</span>, x)\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">use the enumerate function to get the indices too</p>\n\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\"><span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">for</span> i, x <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">in</span> enumerate(nums):\n    print(<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'i= \'</span>, i, <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\' and x= \'</span>, x)\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">to test membership in a list, use the in operator for best performance</p>\n\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\"><span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">if</span> extension <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">in</span> [<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'jpg\'</span>, <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'png\'</span>, <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'svg\'</span>]:\n    print(<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'graphics file\'</span>)\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">use sort to sort a list in place and sorted to return a sorted copy of the list while leaving the original untouched</p>\n\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">l = [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">4</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">2</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">3</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">5</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>]\nm = sorted(l) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># l is still [4,2,3,5,1]</span>\nl.sort() <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># now both m and l are [1,2,3,4,5]</span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">other useful list functions</p>\n\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">len(l) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># returns number of objects in list</span>\nl.count(x) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># returns a number of times x occurs in list</span>\nmax(l) <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">and</span> min(l) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># return max/min of list</span>\nsum(l) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># returns sum of list of summable items</span>\nany(l) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># True if any members evaluate to True</span>\nall(l) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># True if all members evaluate to True</span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"modify-lists\" style=\"margin: 1.3em 0px 1em; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.4em; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: #cccccc;\">modify lists</h2>\n<ul style=\"margin: 1.2em 0px; padding-left: 2em;\">\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">slicing notation can be used to modify a list; just assign a value or sequence of values to the slice</p>\n\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">l = [<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'a\'</span>,<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'b\'</span>,<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'c\'</span>,<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'d\'</span>,<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'e\'</span>]\nl[<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">4</span>] = <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'z\'</span> <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># l is [\'a\',\'b\',\'c\',\'d\',\'z\']</span>\nl[:<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">2</span>] = [<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'v\'</span>, <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'w\'</span>] <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># l is [\'v\',\'w\',\'c\',\'d\',\'z\']</span>\nl[<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">2</span>:<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">4</span>] = [<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'x\'</span>, <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'y\'</span>] <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># l is [\'v\',\'w\',\'x\',\'y\',\'z\']</span>\n</code></pre>\n<ul style=\"margin: 0px; padding-left: 1em;\">\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">to add objects to a list use append, extend, or insert\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">l.append(<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'extra\'</span>) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># adds one element to end of list</span>\nl.extend([<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'extra\'</span>, <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'large\'</span>, <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'fries\'</span>]) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># adds list of elements to end of list</span>\nl.insert(i, x) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># inserts element x at index i</span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">to remove objects from a list, use del, remove, or pop</p>\n\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\"><span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">del</span> l[<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">3</span>] <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># delete fourth item in the list</span>\n<span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">del</span> l[<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">3</span>:<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">5</span>] <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># delete fourth and fifth item in the list</span>\nl.remove(x) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># remove first occurrence of x in the list</span>\nl.pop() <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># delete and return last item in the list</span>\nl.pop(i) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># delete and return item at index i</span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">you can use some operators on lists</p>\n\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">l = [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">2</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">3</span>]\nl += [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">4</span>] <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># concatenation - like l.extend([4]) except returns a new list</span>\nl = [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">0</span>, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>] * <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">3</span> <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># repetition - same as [0, 1] + [0, 1] + [0, 1] or [0, 1, 0, 1, 0, 1]</span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"do-stuff-with-lists\" style=\"margin: 1.3em 0px 1em; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.4em; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: #cccccc;\">do stuff with lists</h2>\n<ul style=\"margin: 1.2em 0px; padding-left: 2em;\">\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">easily implement stack &amp; queue data structures using the methods described above</p>\n\n<ul style=\"margin: 0px; padding-left: 1em;\">\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">stacks\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">stack = [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">2</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">3</span>]\nstack.append(<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">4</span>) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># stack is [1,2,3,4]</span>\nstack.pop() <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># returns 4; stack is [1,2,3]</span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">queues\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">queue = [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">3</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">2</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>]\nqueue.insert(<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">0</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">4</span>) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># queue is [4,3,2,1]</span>\nqueue.pop() <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># returns 1; queue is [4,3,2]</span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">note: inserting items at the beginning of the list is slow compared to the end of the list, so for best performance use Python’s deque class from the collections module for queues</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">string manipulation and analysis using lists</p>\n\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">s = <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'the quick brown fox jumped over the lazy sleeping dog\'</span>\nl = s.split(<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\' \'</span>) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># l is [\'the\', \'quick\', \'brown\', \'fox\', \'jumped\', \'over\', \'the\', \'lazy\', \'sleeping\', \'dog\']</span>\nl = list(set(l)) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># remove duplicates</span>\nl.sort() <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># alphabetize</span>\n<span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">print</span> len(l) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># print number of unique words in s</span>\n<span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">print</span> <span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'\\n\'</span>.join(l) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># print unique words in s, one per line</span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">zip two lists together into a list of tuples</p>\n\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">x_data = [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">3</span>, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">5</span>]\ny_data = [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">2</span>, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">4</span>, <span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">6</span>]\ndata_points = zip(x_data, y_data) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># data_points is [(1, 2), (3, 4), (5, 6)]</span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"list-gotchas\" style=\"margin: 1.3em 0px 1em; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.4em; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; border-bottom-color: #cccccc;\">list gotchas</h2>\n<ul style=\"margin: 1.2em 0px; padding-left: 2em;\">\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">lists as default arguments - default values are evaluated only once, so there are differences in using a mutable type (list, etc.) and an immutable type (None, etc.) as a default</p>\n\n<ul style=\"margin: 0px; padding-left: 1em;\">\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">this function will keep appending char to the same list on subsequent calls\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\"><span class=\"function\" style=\"color: #6699cc;\"><span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">def</span> <span class=\"title\" style=\"color: #999999;\">add_char</span><span class=\"params\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">(char, l=[])</span>:</span>\n    l.append(char)\n<span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">    return</span> l\n<span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">print</span> add_char(<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'*\'</span>) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># [\'*\']</span>\n<span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">print</span> add_char(<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'*\'</span>) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># [\'*\', \'*\']</span>\n<span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">print</span> add_char(<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'*\'</span>) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># [\'*\', \'*\', \'*\']</span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">this function will create a new list on every call\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\"><span class=\"function\" style=\"color: #6699cc;\"><span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">def</span> <span class=\"title\" style=\"color: #999999;\">add_char</span><span class=\"params\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">(char, l=None)</span>:</span>\n<span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">    if</span> l <span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">is</span> <span class=\"built_in\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">None</span>:\n        l = []\n    l.append(char)\n<span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">return</span> l\n<span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">print</span> add_char(<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'*\'</span>) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># [\'*\']</span>\n<span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">print</span> add_char(<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'*\'</span>) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># [\'*\']</span>\n<span class=\"keyword\" style=\"color: #cc99cc;\">print</span> add_char(<span class=\"string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'*\'</span>) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># [\'*\']</span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">assigning a variable to a list does not make a copy of it</p>\n\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">l1 = [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">1</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">2</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">3</span>]\nl2 = [<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">4</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">5</span>,<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">6</span>]\nl2 = l1 <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># now the list [1,2,3] is referenced by both l1 and l2</span>\n<span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># the list [4,5,6] is an object with no references and no way</span>\n<span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># to access it, so it will be automatically deleted (garbage collected)</span>\nl1.append(<span class=\"number\" style=\"color: #f99157;\">4</span>) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># now the value of l1 and l2 is [1,2,3,4]</span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">\n<p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px !important;\">use the list constructor or slicing notation to copy a list</p>\n\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">l2=list(l1) <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># both of these make a copy of l1</span>\nl2=l1[:] <span class=\"comment\" style=\"color: #999999;\"># and assign its reference to l2</span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=\"height: 0; font-size: 0em; padding: 0; margin: 0;\" title=\"MDH:PHA+IyMgaW50cm88L3A+PHA+V2VsY29tZSB0byBteSBQeXRob24gbGlzdHMgcmVmZXJlbmNlIGd1\naWRlLiBUaGUgb2JqZWN0aXZlIGlzIHRvIGdhdGhlciBlc3NlbnRpYWwgaW5mb3JtYXRpb24gb24g\ndGhlIGxpc3QgZGF0YSB0eXBlIGluIG9uZSBwbGFjZSB3aXRoIGxvdHMgb2YgZXhhbXBsZXMuIFBs\nZWFzZSBsZXQgbWUga25vdyB3aGF0IHlvdSB0aGluay4uLmFkZGl0aW9ucywgY29ycmVjdGlvbnMs\nIGFuZCBzdWdnZXN0aW9ucyB3ZWxjb21lITwvcD48cD4jIyBjcmVhdGUgbGlzdHM8L3A+PHA+KiBs\naXN0cyBhcmUgb3JkZXJlZCBzZXF1ZW5jZXMgYW5kIGNhbiBob2xkIGFueSBjb21iaW5hdGlvbiBv\nciB0eXBlcyBvZiBvYmplY3RzIG9yIGV4cHJlc3Npb25zPGJyPiBgYGBweXRob248YnI+IGwgPSBb\nc3R1ZGVudF8xLCA1Njc1NCwgJ2hlbGxvJ108YnI+IGwgPSBbWzEsMiwzXSwgWzQsNSw2XV08YnI+\nIGwgPSBbMSA9PSAyLCAxID09IDFdICMgbCBjb250YWlucyBbRmFsc2UsIFRydWVdPGJyPiBgYGA8\nL3A+PHA+KiBjcmVhdGUgYW4gZW1wdHkgbGlzdDxicj4gYGBgcHl0aG9uPGJyPiBsID0gW108YnI+\nIGwgPSBsaXN0KCkgIyB0aGUgbGlzdCBjb25zdHJ1Y3Rvcjxicj4gYGBgPC9wPjxwPiogY3JlYXRl\nIGEgbGlzdCBieSBhcHBseWluZyBhIGZ1bmN0aW9uIHRvIGV2ZXJ5IG1lbWJlciBvZiBhIHNlcXVl\nbmNlLCBjYWxsZWQgYSBsaXN0IGNvbXByZWhlbnNpb248YnI+IGBgYHB5dGhvbjxicj4gbCA9IFtm\nKHgpIGZvciB4IGluIHNlcXVlbmNlXTx