ommand line with the <code style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0px 0.3em; white-space: pre-wrap; border-radius: 3px; display: inline; background-color: #f8f8f8;\">-c</code> flag; put the code in single quotes and use double quotes in the Python code</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"hljs language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; overflow-x: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">python -c <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'print(\"hi\")\'</span>\r\n</code></pre>\r\n<ul style=\"margin: 1.2em 0px; padding-left: 2em;\">\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">you must print your results in the code to display them in the terminal</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"hljs language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; overflow-x: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">python -c <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'sum([1,2,3,4,5])\'</span> \r\npython -c <span class=\"hljs-string\" style=\"color: #99cc99;\">\'print(sum([1,2,3,4,5]))\'</span>\r\n</code></pre>\r\n<ul style=\"margin: 1.2em 0px; padding-left: 2em;\">\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">you can enter multi-line strings of code</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"hljs language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; overflow-x: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">python -c \'import random\r\nprint(random.randint(1, 10))\'\r\n</code></pre>\r\n<ul style=\"margin: 1.2em 0px; padding-left: 2em;\">\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">but indentation must be preserved</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"hljs language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; overflow-x: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">python -c \'import random\r\n           print(random.randint(1, 10))\'\r\n\r\nFile \"&lt;string&gt;\", line 2\r\n print(random.randint(1, 10))\r\n ^\r\nIndentationError: unexpected indent\r\n</code></pre>\r\n<ul style=\"margin: 1.2em 0px; padding-left: 2em;\">\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">some might find this easier to read</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<pre style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; line-height: 1em; padding: 0px; margin: 1.2em 0px;\"><code class=\"hljs language-python\" style=\"font-size: 0.85em; font-family: Consolas, Inconsolata, Courier, monospace; margin: 0px 0.15em; padding: 0.5em; white-space: pre; border-radius: 3px; display: block; background-color: #f8f8f8; overflow: auto; overflow-x: auto; color: #cccccc; background: #2d2d2d;\">python -c \'\\\r\nimport random\r\nprint(random.randint(1, 10))\r\n\'\r\n</code></pre>\r\n<ul style=\"margin: 1.2em 0px; padding-left: 2em;\">\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px;\">you 